Two people believed to be Zama Zamas were killed and another sustained injuries in a shooting incident. The shooting took place at an old mine along the N12 near New Modder Road in Benoni, on Wednesday afternoon. Benoni is one of the areas in Gauteng Province where illegal mining is rampant. Zama Zamas in the area are also known for often fighting and killing each other over gold. ER24 spokesman said that shortly after 3pm, paramedics from ER24 and Provincial EMS arrived on the scene where they found two men with fatal gunshot wounds. Meiring said there was nothing that could be done for them and they were declared. A third man was found with multiple gunshot wounds to his arms. He was treated on the scene and later transported to a nearby hospital for further care. The exact circumstances surrounding the incident is not yet known. Local authorities attended the scene.